<h2>FAQ</h2>
<h3>工业级羧甲基淀粉可以单独使用吗？</h3>
<p>可在部分配方中单用，但与 HPMC 复配更容易得到稳定的保水和触变表现。</p>
<h3>如何选择粘度等级？</h3>
<p>薄批偏向中低粘度，厚批需更强的抗流挂能力。</p>
<h3>施工季节变化会影响配方吗？</h3>
<p>会，高温或低温都会影响开放时间，建议按季节微调用量。</p>
<p>如需样品或现场配方建议，欢迎联系我们获取工业级羧甲基淀粉方案。</p>`,
    content_en: `<p>On the jobsite, the most common complaints are hard troweling, rapid drying, and powdering. Industrial-grade carboxymethyl starch in putty and wallpaper adhesive supports water retention and thixotropy, helping stabilize the application window and finish quality.</p>
<h2>Link jobsite problems to formulation choices</h2>
<h3>Cracking, dusting, and sandy finish</h3>
<p>These issues are often tied to insufficient water retention and uneven drying.</p>
<h3>Sagging, stringing, and heavy trowel feel</h3>
<p>Typically caused by weak thixotropy or inadequate body.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Check whether open time matches actual work pace</li>
  <li>Observe if the layer sags or strings on the wall</li>
  <li>Compare performance under different temperature and humidity</li>
</ul>
<figure>
  <img src="/images/blog/cms-construction-mix.jpg?v=20251226" alt="Wallpaper adhesive and putty formulation" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
  <figcaption>Stable formulation directly improves application feel.</figcaption>
</figure>
<h2>The CMS + HPMC synergy</h2>
<h3>Water retention and open time</h3>
<p>Industrial-grade CMS boosts water retention. Pairing with HPMC extends open time and reduces rework.</p>
<h3>Cost and batch consistency</h3>
<p>CMS helps balance cost while keeping batch-to-batch performance consistent.</p>
<h2>Recommended mixing and application steps</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Pre-mix dry powder to distribute CMS evenly.</li>
  <li>Add water and mix: low speed for wetting, then medium speed.</li>
  <li>Rest and hydrate to reach a stable system.</li>
  <li>Apply on wall and monitor sagging behavior.</li>
</ol>
<figure>
  <img src="/images/blog/cms-construction-application.jpg?v=20251226" alt="On-site application details" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
  <figcaption>Consistent application steps maximize formulation performance.</figcaption>
</figure>
<h2>Decision matrix: how to prioritize</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Scenario</th>
      <th>CMS focus</th>
      <th>Formulation direction</th>
    </tr>
